eld, Suffolk, England":"Laxfield, Suffolk, England","Laxfield, Mid Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Laxfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fiske","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Norwegian: habitational name from a farm in western Norway, named from Old Norse <i>fiskr</i> ‘fish’ + <i>-e</i> from <i>vin</i> ‘meadow’.","English (East Anglia): variant of   Fisk  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fisk","meanings":["English (East Anglia): metonymic occupational name for a fisherman or fish seller, or a nickname for someone supposedly resembling a fish in some way, from Old Norse <i>fiskr</i> ‘fish’ (cognate with Old English <i>fisc</i>). See   Fish   1."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":55,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Fiske was born in 1400, in Laxfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Hugh Fiske, was 30 and his mother, Katherine Burgess, was 22. He married Joan Lynne about 1447, in Laxfield, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 6 March 1462, in Laxfield, Suffolk, England, at the age of 62, and was buried in Laxfield, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"1400–15 March 1462":"1400–15. märts 1462","1397–1464":"1397–1464","1400–1462":"1400–1462","1401–Male":"1401–Surnud","1427–1504":"1427–1504","1445–1505":"1445–1505","1370–1435":"1370–1435","1378–1399":"1378–1399","1 December 1435":"1. detsember 1435","1462":"1462","1370":"1370","15 March 1462":"15. märts 1462","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","April 1398":"aprill 1398","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1399":"1399","1464":"1464","about 1447":"umbes 1447","1397":"1397","1505":"1505","about 1395":"umbes 1395","1504":"1504","1427":"1427","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Laxfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Laxfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Laxfield, Suffolk, England":"Laxfield, Suffolk, England","Laxfield, Mid Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Laxfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1400–15 March 1462":"1400–15. maaliskuuta 1462","1397–1464":"1397–1464","1400–1462":"1400–1462","1401–Male":"1401–Kuollut","1427–1504":"1427–1504","1445–1505":"1445–1505","1370–1435":"1370–1435","1378–1399":"1378–1399","1 December 1435":"1. joulukuuta 1435","1462":"1462","1370":"1370","15 March 1462":"15. maaliskuuta 1462","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","April 1398":"huhtikuu 1398","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1399":"1399","1464":"1464","about 1447":"noin 1447","1397":"1397","1505":"1505","about 1395":"noin 1395","1504":"1504","1427":"1427","Suffolk, England